  Scenario: testing Last.fm Join page Password Field
    Given open last.fm join page and accepted cookies
    When User fills out password field with "A"
    Then Comment about incorrection pops out

    When User fills out password field with "Blabl3"
    Then Comment about incorrection pops out

    When User fills out password field with "Blabl*-"
    Then Comment about incorrection pops out

    When User fills out password field with "/*-/*-"
    Then Comment about incorrection pops out

    When User fills out password field with "123456"
    Then Comment about incorrection pops out

    When User fills out password field with "    "
    Then Comment about incorrection pops out

  Scenario: testing Last.fm Join page Field skipped
    Given open last.fm join page and accepted cookies
    When User fills out all fields correct, but passes Username field
    Then Comment asking to fill in the field pops out

    When User fills out all fields correct, but passes Email field
    Then Comment asking to fill in the field pops out

    When User fills out all fields correct, but passes Password field
    Then Comment asking to fill in the field pops out

    When User fills out all fields correct, but passes Confirm Password field
    Then Comment asking to fill in the field pops out

    When User fills out all fields correct, but don't ticks the captcha box
    Then Comment 'You didn't complete the captcha properly. Try again?' pops out

    When User fills out all fields correct, but don't ticks the terms box
    Then Comment 'Not quite so fast! Please agree to these terms first.' pops out



  Scenario: testing Last.fm Join page misspell password
    Given open last.fm join page and accepted cookies
    When User fills out all fields correct, but misspells in Confirm Password field
    Then Comment  that Passwords don't match

  Scenario: testing Last.fm Join page while being already assigned / already used
    Given open last.fm join page and accepted cookies
    When User fills out Username field with used username
    Then Comment 'Sorry, this username isn't available.' pops out

    When User fills out Email field with used e-mail address
    Then Comment 'Sorry, that email address is already registered to another account.' pops out
